cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.SE 

The paper discusses parallel algorithms for on-the-fly model checking of LTL properties, which is a topic related to formal verification and model checking. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). The paper also discusses parallelization techniques and optimization strategies, which are relevant to parallel computing (cs.PL - Programming Languages, cs.DC - Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). Additionally, the paper uses a statistical model to analyze the performance of the algorithms, which is related to data structures and algorithms (cs.DS - Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper evaluates the algorithms on a specific software tool (LTSmin), which is related to software engineering (cs.SE - Software Engineering).
